  faqs={[
    { question: "How do I check my AJK electricity bill online in March 2026?", answer: "Enter your 14-digit AJKED reference number in the bill checker at the top of this page and click Check Bill. Your complete AJK electricity bill for March 2026 appears in seconds — showing amount due, due date, units consumed, and all charges. This works for all AJK districts including Muzaffarabad, Mirpur, Rawalakot, Kotli, Bagh, and Neelum Valley. Free, no login, 24/7." },
    { question: "What is the AJKED helpline number?", answer: "The AJKED (AJK Electricity Department) helpline is 1912 — NOT 118 which is the mainland WAPDA helpline. For any AJK billing dispute, connection issue, or outage, call 1912. This number is specific to Azad Kashmir and connects directly to AJKED's customer service. The 1912 number works from all mobile networks and landlines within Pakistan." },
    { question: "Why is the AJK electricity tariff lower than Pakistan's?", answer: "AJK benefits from locally generated hydropower from two major sources: Mangla Dam (1,000+ MW on the Jhelum river at Mirpur) and Neelum-Jhelum Hydropower Project (969 MW near Muzaffarabad). Hydro generation has near-zero fuel cost unlike thermal plants. AJK's government policy channels this benefit to AJK consumers through a special lifeline rate of Rs 5.79/unit for the first 50 units — the lowest electricity rate in Pakistan." },
    { question: "How do I check my AJK bill for Mirpur?", answer: "Mirpur is within AJKED's service area — enter your 14-digit reference number in the checker above. Mirpur City, New Mirpur, Dadyal, and Chakswari all fall under AJKED's Mirpur Circle. Mirpur is AJK's most populous and economically active district. The same 14-digit reference number format applies as for all AJKED connections." },
    { question: "How do I check my AJK bill for Rawalakot?", answer: "Rawalakot (Poonch district) is under AJKED's Poonch Circle. Enter your 14-digit reference number in the checker above — it works for Rawalakot City, Hajira, Plandri, and all Poonch district consumers. Rawalakot at 1,676m elevation has a cool climate and most consumers there maintain Protected status without AC." },
    { question: "How do I check my AJK bill for the Neelum Valley?", answer: "Neelum Valley (including Athmuqam, Sharda, and Kel) is under AJKED's Muzaffarabad Circle. Enter your reference number in the checker above. Neelum Valley is one of Pakistan's most scenic areas, powered significantly by the Neelum-Jhelum Hydropower Project which sits at the mouth of the valley near Muzaffarabad." },
    { question: "How do I download my AJKED duplicate bill?", answer: "After your AJK bill loads in the checker, click Download PDF. Select Save as PDF in the print dialog and click Save. Your AJKED duplicate bill downloads instantly as a PDF — ready to pay at JazzCash, Easypaisa, HBL, or any bank in Muzaffarabad, Mirpur, Rawalakot, or your AJK city." },
    { question: "How do I pay my AJK electricity bill online?", answer: "Pay through JazzCash, Easypaisa, HBL, or any bank mobile app. Go to Bill Payments, select Electricity, choose AJK or WAPDA, enter your 14-digit reference number, verify the amount, and confirm. Online payment reaches AJKED's system within 2 to 4 hours. JazzCash and Easypaisa have good coverage across AJK's major cities." },
    { question: "What is the grace period for AJK electricity bill payment?", answer: "AJKED gives 7 days after the due date to pay without a late payment surcharge. After the grace period, a 10% late payment surcharge applies to the unpaid amount. Check your due date online using this tool — do not rely solely on paper bills arriving in remote valley areas." },
    { question: "Is AJK regulated by NEPRA?", answer: "AJK is not directly under NEPRA's regulatory jurisdiction. Electricity tariffs and service standards in AJK are set by the Azad Kashmir Council and the AJK government through AJKED. Consumers in AJK cannot directly use NEPRA's consumer complaint mechanism (0800-63000) for AJKED issues — instead, call 1912 and escalate within AJK government channels. NEPRA does coordinate with AJKED on national-level policy but does not directly regulate AJKED tariffs." },
    { question: "How do I file a billing complaint with AJKED?", answer: "Call AJKED helpline 1912 with your reference number. Explain the complaint and get a written acknowledgment or CRN if available. Visit the nearest AJKED divisional office in Muzaffarabad, Mirpur, or Rawalakot for complex billing disputes. Since AJK is outside NEPRA's direct jurisdiction, escalate unresolved complaints to the AJK government's electricity authority or the Wafaqi Mohtasib." },
  ]}

